President Obama announced his intent to nominate Deborah K. Jones as the Ambassador to Libya and James Knight as the Ambassador to the Republic of Chad. He also announced his intent to appoint Lesley Weiss as a member and Chair of the Commission for the Preservation of America's Heritage Abroad. Deborah K. Jones is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has previously served as the U.S. Ambassador to Kuwait. James Knight is also a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and has served as the U.S. Ambassador to Benin. Lesley Weiss is the Director of Community Services and Cultural Affairs for NCSJ: Advocates on Behalf of Jews in Russia, Ukraine, the Baltic States & Eurasia. She was appointed to the Commission for the Preservation of America's Heritage Abroad by President Obama in 2011 and became the Chair in 2013.